FIG. 9 shows the operating lever in an opening control position;


FIG. 10 shows the operating lever in a closing control position;


FIG. 11 shows a countergear lever arranged between the operating lever and an engagement cam of the frame in a plugged-in position;


FIG. 12 shows the countergear lever acting on the operating lever when plugout takes place;


FIG. 13 is a perspective view of a securing latch of the operating lever;


FIG. 14 is a view of a countergear lever designed to operate in conjunction with an operating lever according to a second embodiment of the invention, in a plugged-in state of the switchgear apparatus;


FIG. 15 is a view of the countergear lever operating in conjunction with the operating lever according to the second embodiment of the invention, when the circuit breaker leaves its plugged-in position;


FIG. 16 is a view of a countergear lever according to a third embodiment of the invention.
